title.narrative: 1.2: COMMUNITY-BASED INTEGRATED EARLY CHILDHOOD CARE AND DEVELOPMENT SERVICES

description.narrative: Communities in priority districts and regions have increased capacity to deliver community-based services, create demand and ensure accountability for integrated early childhood survival and development services., which contributes to Child Health, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Early Childhood Development, Early Childhood Development (Covid), Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid), Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid), Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Young girls and boys (0â€“5 years), particularly the most deprived and hard-to-reach, are immunized, well nourished, healthy, protected, registered at birth and prepared for school, including in humanitarian situations.
